(134, 1, '2014-01-18 19:13:13', '2014-01-18 19:13:13', 'LOS ANGELES - February 14, 2013 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartment solutions, has been selected as winner of the 2013 Tower of Excellence Most Creative Marketing award presented by the Corporate Housing Providers Association. This honor recognizes an outstanding marketing concept that has greatly impacted corporate housing in the past year. Oakwood Worldwide received this recognition at CHPA''s annual conference on February 5, 2013, at the Arizona Biltmore in Phoenix. This is the fourth CHPA Tower of Excellence Award - Most Creative Marketing for Oakwood Worldwide in the past six years.\r\n\r\nOakwood Worldwide''s winning submission was selected from four nominees in the "more than 300 units" category, based on its ability to successfully communicate the benefit to companies in choosing Oakwood for global corporate housing solutions, while raising awareness and promoting the value of corporate housing to a wider audience. The company''s marketing campaign was designed to gain business from prospects and regain business from inactive accounts. The campaign combined a traditional incentive mailing with a targeted email, employing the use of personalized URLs to track leads. To date, the program can claim a more than 2,300 percent return on investment.\r\n\r\n"The campaign demonstrates the powerful results of a true collaboration between sales and marketing," said Jill Chapman, Oakwood Worldwide senior vice president of sales and marketing. "Our marketing team continues to successfully raise our visibility in the industry, driving rentals, increasing revenue and opening doors to even the toughest prospects."', 'Oakwood Worldwide&reg; Captures Industry Award for Marketing', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-captures-industry-award-for-marketing', '', '', '2014-01-21 18:01:58', '2014-01-21 18:01:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=134', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(135, 1, '2014-01-19 19:17:38', '2014-01-19 19:17:38', 'LOS ANGELES - February 25, 2013 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartment solutions, announces the promotion of Lisa Rauch to director of sales for its Asia Pacific region. Rauch will be responsible for setting the regional sales strategy in alignment with the company''s global strategy.\r\n\r\nRauch replaces Craig Ryan, who recently took a newly created role as managing director for the region. This change was part of a recently announced organizational model that combines the company''s expert knowledge of local markets with its global leadership in the corporate housing and serviced apartment industry. Rauch will focus on achieving defined sales objectives, delivering effective client solutions and providing leadership for the APAC sales team.\r\n\r\n"Bringing Lisa into this role further strengthens our on-the-ground presence and sales capability in the region," said Oakwood Worldwide APAC managing director Craig Ryan. "She''s an excellent leader with the ability to accelerate sales growth, increase our market share and expand our global footprint."\r\n\r\nRauch joined Oakwood Worldwide in 2003. She has held a number of sales and account management roles - most recently as account executive for the Southern California region. She is a multi-year recipient of numerous sales awards within Oakwood Worldwide, including the President''s Club. She holds a bachelor''s degree from Pennsylvania State University.\r\n\r\nRauch will operate out of Oakwood Worldwide''s sales and service center in Singapore and can be reached at +65 6336 6900.', 'Oakwood Worldwide&reg; Announces New Director of Sales for Asia Pacific Region', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-announces-new-director-of-sales-for-asia-pacific-region', '', '', '2014-01-21 18:01:46', '2014-01-21 18:01:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=135', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
