(143, 1, '2014-01-15 19:58:46', '2014-01-15 19:58:46', 'LOS ANGELES - May 13, 2013 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartments, announces the addition of Katie Lim as director of supplier management for its <A href="http://www.oakwood.com/cms/asia-pacific.html">Asia Pacific region.</a> She will be responsible for driving the regional growth of the business through strategic supplier relationships.\r\n\r\nThis position is part of the company''s commitment to developing in-region expertise to support an evolving global business environment. As part of her responsibilities, Lim will focus on sourcing and contracting with new suppliers, negotiating favorable terms, enforcing service-level agreement requirements and implementing standard processes across the region.\r\n\r\nLim has extensive experience in account management and sales, having held a number of senior positions throughout her career. Prior to joining Oakwood, Lim was assistant director of sales for The Ascott Limited management group based in Singapore.\r\n\r\nLim received her bachelor''s degree in tourism management and arts from the Curtin University of Technology in Australia. She will operate out of Oakwood Worldwide''s sales and service center in Singapore and can be reached at +65 6521 6382.', 'Oakwood Worldwide&reg; Announces New Director of Supplier Management for Asia Pacific Region', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-announces-new-director-of-supplier-management-for-asia-pacific-region', '', '', '2014-01-21 18:02:40', '2014-01-21 18:02:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=143', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
