(193, 1, '2014-01-21 18:22:49', '2014-01-21 18:22:49', 'A visionary, a leader and a gentleman. Howard Ruby, the Founder, Chairman and CEO of Oakwood Worldwide, has embodied all three roles while guiding the firm through its 52-year evolution into a multi-billion-dollar real estate company, and the global leader in the hospitality niche of serviced apartments.\r\n\r\nToday, Oakwood Worldwide operates throughout North America, Asia and Europe. Oakwood''s annual gross earnings exceed $600 million. The firm has 3,000 employees, and manages 20,000 serviced apartments.\r\n\r\nRuby''s biography parallels that of Oakwood. In 1960, Ruby and business partner Bob Franks began managing small apartment buildings in California, quickly establishing techniques to improve a building''s customer service and return-on-investment. Later, with a third partner, Ed Broida, they developed several niche real estate concepts, including Bay Village Apartments (for families), and the lucrative South Bay Clubs (for singles).\r\n\r\nIn 1969, Ruby created the Oakwood Apartments brand, featuring furnished apartment complexes that catered to a broader audience including business travelers, families, seniors and more. The concept of "serviced apartments" was born and for the first time, extended stay travelers had a spacious alternative to staying in a hotel room.\r\n\r\nThe 1970s and 1980s brought further growth as the Oakwood brand continued to gain footing across the United States. Ruby led the company into commercial real estate, real estate fee management, telecommunications, and "home services," the housewares division that supplies linens, dishes, and other such items that make a furnished apartment a home.\r\n\r\nRuby was founding member of the National Multi-Housing Council (NMHC), today one of the most established trade groups in the U.S. apartment industry.\r\n\r\nThe 1990s brought the largest growth surge ever to Oakwood, as the Oakwood Corporate Housing service expanded throughout the United States, serving virtually every city nationwide.\r\n\r\nIn 1995, Ruby made the decision to expand Oakwood globally, and made frequent visits to Asia and Europe to introduce the Oakwood concept. In 1997, he was the keynote speaker for the Horwath Serviced Apartment Conference in Hong Kong.\r\n\r\nSoon after, the Oakwood concept spread its wings with expansion into Singapore, Thailand, China, Korea, Philippines, Japan, and the United Kingdom. The company created two new brands, Oakwood Premier (five-star) and Oakwood Residence (four-star), and opened spectacular new buildings in Asia. Further expansion is foreseen in Asia and Europe.\r\n\r\nHoward Ruby remains the firm''s beloved guiding visionary, leading Oakwood''s global growth, technology innovation, and focus on customer service. Every year he travels the world, visiting Oakwood offices to motivate his employees and meet with partners.\r\n\r\nRuby has also traveled the world many times to expand his already impressive photography portfolio. After numerous trips to the Arctic to photograph polar bears, he witnessed the effects of climate change firsthand and was moved to partner with National Wildlife Federation to develop an educational outreach program. This program uses his emotional and dramatic photographs of melting ice and threatened polar bears to educate children as well as adults. Many Oakwood employees volunteered in classrooms as part of this program. Visit www.climateclassroomkids.org for more information.\r\n\r\nIn addition to a special exhibit at the Smithsonian Museum of Natural History where he was named "International Conservation Photographer of the Year" by National Wildlife Federation (NWF), Howard has donated major bodies of his work to the UCLA Ronald Reagan Hospital and the UC Santa Barbara Donald Bren School of Environmental Science and Management.\r\n\r\nRuby is a graduate of the University of Pennsylvania''s prestigious Wharton School of Business. He is married to actress Yvette Mimieux, and is a father of four and grandfather of six.', 'Howard Ruby', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'howard-ruby', '', '', '2014-01-21 18:22:49', '2014-01-21 18:22:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=193', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
(194, 1, '2014-01-16 18:23:41', '2014-01-16 18:23:41', 'As president of Oakwood Worldwide, Ric Villarreal leads the company''s Executive Committee who, together, implement Oakwood Worldwide''s strategic plan. They are committed to continuing market leadership through strategic growth aligned with client needs and forged by Oakwood Worldwide''s world-class Associates. This innovative leadership team has re-energized the organization with connectivity, transparency and clarity of vision.\r\n\r\nVillarreal''s leadership philosophy centers on organizational alignment with a clear corporate vision and empowered Associates who understand their responsibilities and levels of accountability. Under his leadership, Oakwood Worldwide has been transformed into a company that is connected to the voice of the customer more than ever before. Villarreal is a collaborative team builder who seeks the input of the Associates closest to the Oakwood Worldwide customer experience. He strives to make the company a great place to work where people are inspired to be their best.\r\n\r\nVillarreal joined Oakwood Worldwide in 1997 with a mission to redesign new business processes for the company''s corporate housing division. During his tenure, he has immersed himself in understanding company processes and driving both technical and business innovation. He has served as senior vice president and chief information officer and also oversaw human resources efforts for a period of time. Additionally, he was responsible for directing call center operations for the Oakwood Worldwide Sales and Service Center in Phoenix, Ariz. Throughout his career at Oakwood Worldwide, Villarreal has looked for every opportunity to get in front of the customer and to better understand the issues and opportunities that their input brings. The experience of being immersed in all of these company efforts led to his eventual appointment to president of Oakwood Worldwide in 2009.\r\n\r\nSince then, Oakwood Worldwide has continued its global expansion with both long-term, master-leased corporate apartments and an international supplier network of leased apartments. In 2012, Oakwood Worldwide acquired the ExecuStay® brand from Marriott International, further expanding its corporate apartment portfolio in the United States. In 2013, Oakwood Worldwide announced the creation of Insurance Housing Solutions™, offering the value of a one-stop shop for temporary housing to the insurance industry.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Oakwood Worldwide, Villarreal had a successful 16-year career at Xerox Corporation. He was part of the company''s first total quality management initiative, which won the Malcolm Baldrige National Quality award. During his tenure there, he worked across a number of divisions in various capacities – always with a focus on process and team building. His career at Xerox laid the foundation for Villarreal''s successful experiences at Oakwood Worldwide as a technical leader, call center manager, and training and sales manager. Combined, these experiences have enriched his perspective and helped to guide the company''s focus on the voice of the customer.\r\n\r\nA resident of Los Angeles, Calif., Villarreal and his wife Cindy love to travel to places they have never been, seeking out the richness and sweetness of new cultures. ', 'Ric Villarreal', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ric-villarreal', '', '', '2014-01-21 19:33:13', '2014-01-21 19:33:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=194', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
(195, 1, '2014-01-17 18:25:12', '2014-01-17 18:25:12', 'Jill Chapman is senior vice president of global sales and marketing for Oakwood Worldwide. She leads sales and marketing strategy, while managing global operations outside the United States. Her responsibilities include strengthening the Oakwood Worldwide family of brands, and delivering targeted, client-driven solutions.\r\n\r\nChapman brings more than 25 years of dynamic sales leadership and customer service experience to this position. Previously, she served as vice president of sales for Oakwood Worldwide''s western region, during which time she helped bring innovative customer and sales solutions to many Fortune 1000 companies.\r\n\r\nBefore joining Oakwood Worldwide, Jill held business development and sales management positions at RR Donnelley with progressive responsibility over an 18-year period. As regional sales manager there, she consistently grew revenue and was accomplished around talent development. Three of her associates received the company''s Rookie of the Year award with three other associates winning Sales Associate of the Year awards.\r\n\r\nChapman earned her bachelor''s degree in American Studies from Florida State University. A resident of Southern California, Chapman is involved with volunteer work at her children''s schools as well as fundraising for community service organizations that benefit women''s shelters and families with medical emergencies.\r\n\r\nHer favorite place to travel? Sri Lanka, because of the beautiful country and the people who are so charming and friendly.', 'Jill Chapman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jill-chapman', '', '', '2014-01-21 19:34:13', '2014-01-21 19:34:13', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=195', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
(196, 1, '2014-01-15 18:26:02', '2014-01-15 18:26:02', 'Bill Foltz is an experienced senior executive with a strong background in growing and operating holding companies with expertise in M&A, corporate finance, private equity, fundraising, and professional sports.\r\n\r\nBill is currently CFO of Oakwood Temporary Housing, the largest provider of temporary housing in the world. He joined Oakwood in February, 2009 assuming oversight of Treasury, Finance, Risk Management and Strategic Planning. He serves on the Executive Committee.\r\n\r\nEarlier in Bill''s career, he served as CFO of the Los Angeles Dodgers professional baseball club where he spent 10 years as a key member of the management team. In addition to being a member of the executive team responsible for the sale of the club to News Corp., he had operational responsibility over all aspects of the clubs day to day operations. Prior to joining the Dodgers, Bill was a manager for the public accounting firm of Ernst & Young and is a CPA.\r\n\r\nFollowing the Dodgers, Bill was CFO and a Principal of Platinum Equity Capital Partners, one of the fastest growing private equity firms in the nation. Bill oversaw the firm''s growth from approximately 30 people to over 180 employees, while Platinum expanded its portfolio investments from $175 million in ttm revenues in 1998 to over $4 billion in 2003. During this period, Bill had operational responsibility over Platinum''s 27 wholly-owned subsidiaries, was a member of the investment committee, and participated in almost all of the firm''s approximately 35 transactions during his tenure, overseeing the integration of the new acquisitions into the portfolio. Bill also managed the company''s initial private equity fundraising of $700 million.\r\n\r\nAs a SVP of Roll International, Bill oversaw the portfolio of seven wholly owned companies in consumer products, such as iconic consumer brands like Fiji Water and PomWonderful Pomegranate Juice. In addition to oversight for this $1 billion portfolio, Bill oversaw the business development group that led the acquisition of Fiji Water in November 2004.\r\n\r\nImmediately prior to joining Oakwood, Bill was CFO of Gorilla Nation Media, one of the largest online advertising representation firms in the world. He oversaw the Finance, Accounting and HR departments. While at Gorilla, he successfully led the company''s second round fundraising.', 'Bill Foltz', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bill-foltz', '', '', '2014-01-21 19:32:46', '2014-01-21 19:32:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=196', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
(197, 1, '2014-01-14 18:27:03', '2014-01-14 18:27:03', 'Marina Lubinsky is senior vice president and chief information officer for Oakwood Worldwide. Lubinsky leads Oakwood Worldwide''s information technology function and is responsible for strategy, deployment, and operations of technology both regionally and globally. As part of these responsibilities, she directs the implementation of key programs and initiatives that enable the company''s strategic plans.\r\n\r\nLubinsky joined Oakwood in 2006 as vice president of information technology. During her tenure in that role, she successfully directed the design and development of the company''s technology platforms, resulting in increased reliability, significant cost savings and much-improved customer care. In 2009, Lubinsky was named to her current position and where she is focused on delivering application and infrastructure technology that help the company effectively meet and respond to customer needs.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Oakwood, Lubinsky worked as a corporate IT executive as well as an information technology consultant. She also has experience in system development, distributed computing, networks, general technology infrastructure and business process re-engineering. Her background includes IT leadership positions with AIG, Disney and Accenture.\r\n\r\nLubinsky holds a Master of Science degree in electrical and computer engineering from the Technical University of Denmark, Copenhagen. She also completed an executive management program at Northwestern University''s Kellogg School of Management and was named a Kellogg Executive Scholar. Lubinsky is a member of the CIO Executive Council and the National Association of Professional Women.\r\n', 'Marina Lubinsky', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'marina-lubinsky', '', '', '2014-01-21 19:33:45', '2014-01-21 19:33:45', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=197', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
(198, 1, '2014-01-14 18:27:53', '2014-01-14 18:27:53', 'Ana Castellanos is a senior human resources executive with over 20 years of human resources and training experience in the hospitality and customer service industry.\r\n\r\nAs the Vice President of Human Resources for Oakwood Worldwide, Ms. Castellanos directly oversees all human resources functional areas including talent acquisition, learning & development, employee relations, compliance & legal, compensation & benefits and internal communications.\r\n\r\nMs. Castellanos'' career started in the hospitality industry, where she worked for major hotel companies originally in operations, later moving to human resources. She helped open various hotels, casinos and major retail stores where she managed the human resources function including talent sourcing & recruiting, training & development, career planning, succession management and employee relations.', 'Ana Castellanos', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ana-castellanos', '', '', '2014-01-21 19:31:00', '2014-01-21 19:31:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=executive_committee&#038;p=198', 0, 'executive_committee', '', 0),
